    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Light three-wheeled, hooded vehicles that serve as taxis. Originally found in southern and eastern Asia, now popular elsewhere. The form grew out of the rickshaw, which was pulled by men on foot.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
